# IqUp-V2 — environment variable shapes (NO real secrets).
#
# This repo is PUBLIC. Real keys live ONLY in Vercel's environment settings,
# server-side — never in the code and never in a committed file. Copy this file
# to `.env.local` (gitignored) for local work and fill in real values there.
#
# Supabase (the anonymous scores DB) is wired as of Phase 2.01; the rest below are
# placeholders for the integrations that arrive in later Part-2 phases. Each is
# added in the phase noted next to it.

# --- App ---
# Public base URL of the app (used for absolute links / OG tags).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL="http://localhost:3000"
# Deployment environment stamped onto each anonymous score row (data hygiene, so
# preview/test rows can be excluded from real norms later). One of:
# development | preview | production. Unset ⇒ development. — Phase 2.01
APP_ENV="development"

# --- Supabase (anonymous scores + admin auth) — Phase 2.01 / 2.04 ---
# Runtime (read by the app):
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=""
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=""
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=""     # server-side ONLY — bypasses RLS; never client-exposed
# CLI / migrations only (NOT read by the app at runtime) — `supabase db push`:
SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF=""
SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=""           # server-side ONLY — used to apply migrations

# --- Brevo (leads + transactional PDF email) — Phase 2.02 ---
# Server-side transactional e-mail + parent-contact upsert. The API key is a
# SECRET (server-only); the sender + list IDs are non-secret. List selection
# follows APP_ENV: production → list 7, everything else (dev/preview) → list 8.
BREVO_API_KEY=""                          # SECRET — server-side only
BREVO_SENDER_EMAIL="noreply@iqup.mk"      # usable once iqup.mk is DNS-authenticated
BREVO_SENDER_NAME="IQ UP!"                # quoted: contains a space
BREVO_LIST_ID_PRODUCTION="7"
BREVO_LIST_ID_TEST="8"

# --- Meta Pixel + Conversions API — Phase 2.03 ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_META_PIXEL_ID=""
# META_CAPI_ACCESS_TOKEN=""      # server-side only

# --- GA4 — Phase 2.03 ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GA4_MEASUREMENT_ID=""

# --- Booking CTA (client-provided) — wired in Phase 1.08, real URL before launch ---
# The confirmation CTA links out as {NEXT_PUBLIC_BOOKING_URL}?grad={city}. NOT a
# secret. When unset, the app falls back to a clearly-marked placeholder
# (`https://booking.example.invalid`, see src/features/lead/cta.ts). The real
# booking URL is a pending Cowork asset.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BOOKING_URL="https://booking.example.invalid"
